@startuml use-cases-data-lifecycle
title trawhile — Data Lifecycle (Epic 8)

note as N
  Epic 8 combines a user-facing privacy step with
  automated scrubbing and purge behavior.

  The first-login GDPR notice flow (UR-F060) is shown in
  use-cases-account.puml and seq-first-login.puml.

  Retention periods and node retention are configured via
  the system config file, including the purge schedule
  (SR-F050.F05).

  Activity purge (SR-F050.F01/F02) runs at the configured
  purge schedule in the company timezone, deleting whatever
  crossed the rolling retention cutoff as of that run.
  Node deletion (SR-F050.F03/F04) runs immediately after
  each scheduled activity purge. Both jobs are idempotent
  and resume on application restart using stored cutoff_date.

  Invitation auto-expiry (SR-C010.C01) runs daily,
  transitioning users with expired pending_invitations
  to the Ready for Scrubbing state; cleanup is then
  executed by SR-F070.F01.

  See state-purge-lifecycle.puml and
  state-user-lifecycle.puml for entity lifecycle states
  and cross-entity deletion dependencies.
end note

@enduml
